vec.truncate(2);
assert_eq!(vec, [1, 2]);
```

[Run](https://play.rust-lang.org/?code=%23!%5Ballow(unused)%5D%0Afn+main()+%7B%0A++++let+mut+vec+=+vec!%5B1,+2,+3,+4,+5%5D;%0A++++vec.truncate(2);%0A++++assert_eq!(vec,+%5B1,+2%5D);%0A%7D&edition=2021)

No truncation occurs when `len` is greater than the vector‚Äôs current length:

```
