Clones and appends all elements in a slice to the `Vec`.

Iterates over the slice `other`, clones each element, and then appends it to this `Vec`. The `other` slice is traversed in-order.

Note that this function is same as [`extend`](about:blank/struct.Vec.html#method.extend "method std::vec::Vec::extend") except that it is specialized to work with slices instead. If and when Rust gets specialization this function will likely be deprecated (but still available).

