Returns a reference to an element or subslice, without doing bounds checking.

For a safe alternative see [`get`](about:blank/primitive.slice.html#method.get "method slice::get").

##### [¬ß](#safety-3)Safety

Calling this method with an out-of-bounds index is _[undefined behavior](https://doc.rust-lang.org/reference/behavior-considered-undefined.html)_ even if the resulting reference is not used.

You can think of this like `.get(index).unwrap_unchecked()`. It‚Äôs UB to call `.get_unchecked(len)`, even if you immediately convert to a pointer. And it‚Äôs UB to call `.get_unchecked(..len + 1)`, `.get_unchecked(..=len)`, or similar.

##### [¬ß](#examples-75)Examples

```
let x = &[1, 2, 4];

unsafe {
    assert_eq!(x.get_unchecked(1), &2);
}
```

[Run](https://play.rust-lang.org/?code=%23!%5Ballow(unused)%5D%0Afn+main()+%7B%0A++++let+x+=+%26%5B1,+2,+4%5D;%0A++++%0A++++unsafe+%7B%0A++++++++assert_eq!(x.get_unchecked(1),+%262);%0A++++%7D%0A%7D&edition=2021)

